> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Of Berkshire was born about 1154, in England. She married Robert Driby about 1174. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1194."},"et":{"about 1154–after 1194":"umbes 1154–pärast 1194","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1175–1215":"1175–1215","1154–1194":"1154–1194","Abt 1174":"umbes 1174","1215":"1215","after 1194":"pärast 1194","1154":"1154","1175":"1175","about 1154":"umbes 1154","1194":"1194","1150":"1150","about 1175":"umbes 1175","Driby, Lincolnshire, England":"Driby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1154–after 1194":"noin 1154–1194 jälkeen","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1175–1215":"1175–1215","1154–1194":"1154–1194","Abt 1174":"noin 1174","1215":"1215","after 1194":"1194 jälkeen","1154":"1154","1175":"1175","about 1154":"noin 1154","1194":"1194","1150":"1150","about 1175":"noin 1175","Driby, Lincolnshire, England":"Driby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"Engla